    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get the \"ongoing struggle\" part, but like, some people say the movement actually did way more than just laws—like it fundamentally changed the country's values. others say the tactics used back then were actually pretty divisive and caused a lot of the backlash we see today. as a history prof, how do you weigh those different views? is there a \"correct\" way to look at why it happened the way it did?",
