      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A nuanced view acknowledges that the movement was both a catalyst for fundamental moral change and a politically complicated event. The infusion of nonviolent philosophy into American public discourse undeniably shifted national values toward greater ideals of equality. However, the tactics employed, particularly the confrontational nature of some protests, certainly provoked significant and lasting resistance and backlash from opposing groups. In history, there is rarely one \"correct\" way; instead, understanding the tension between moral victories and political fractures provides the richest analysis.",
